{
  "doc_id": "36386",
  "text": "As for research, patient involvement avoids wasted research with outcomes that are irrelevant to patients and their relatives and carers [CITATION_1] . A recent systematic review of clinical trials in several specialities showed that only 16 % (1:6) reported that the public had been involved in selecting outcome measures; indicating the need for good methodological guidance to improve upon this [CITATION_2] . The Core Outcome Measures for Effectiveness Trials (COMET) initiative entails the development and adoption of a core outcome set (COS) for each health area as a minimum for all trials. This will not only enable comparison, but will also ensure the relevance of the outcome measures to all stakeholders, especially patients and members of the public [CITATION_3] .",
